		<h4>About eDiVa </h4>
		<p>
			eDiVA ("Exome Disease Variant Analysis") is a platform for variant annotation and prioritization, which integrates multiple genomic and clinical information sources to identify 
			disease-causing variants. eDiVA uses a novel machine-learning based damage pathogenicity classifier (eDiVA-Score) that facilitates ranking of the most likely candidate variants and 
			genes. Clinical information and clinical phenotypes are used to further prioritize candidate variants. eDiVA's prioritization algorithm has been optimized for the analysis of rare 
			genetic diseases in parent-child trios and other family settings, using variant segregation analysis to pinpoint the causal variant in a completely automated manor.
		</p>
